{"type":"message","id":"97776c4c","parentId":"e3dfc1e6","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:07:02.586Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_l7mswgqm3h9a_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 050621\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n- Key insight: Compression and Causal Discovery are the SAME problem\r\n- Next action: Implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe pending TIC experiment requires:\r\n1. Implementing TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n2. Measuring invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n3. Predicting next pulse content from invariants\r\n4. Validating against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nI should create the TIC experiment code. Let me look at what files exist and create a practical implementation.\r\n\r\nLet me first check what's in the logs directory and the research directory to understand the structure better.\r\n\r\nGiven the goals, I need to:\r\n1. Create a TIC classifier implementation\r\n2. This should analyze pulse logs to find invariant vs variant patterns\r\n3. Test prediction of next pulse content\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete action that advances the Phase 1 advancement goal. Let me create a Python script that implements the TIC classifier.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment is the critical next step to validate the Compression-Causal Duality hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns across pulse logs and tests next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `tic/tic_classifier.py` - the Temporal Invariance Compression classifier that will analyze pulse logs, classify content as invariant/variant, and test prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```python\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\r\nSuccess Criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nclass TICClassifier:\r\n    \"\"\"Classifies pulse content as invariant (causal) or variant (accidental).\"\"\"\r\n    \r\n    def __init__(self, log_dir=\"logs\"):\r\n        self.log_dir = Path(log_dir)\r\n        self.pulses = []\r\n        self.invariants = {}  # pattern -> frequency\r\n        self.variants = {}    # pattern -> frequency\r\n        \r\n    def load_pulses(self):\r\n        \"\"\"Load all pulse log files.\"\"\"\r\n        for f in sorted(self.log_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\")):\r\n            content = f.read_text()\r\n            self.pulses.append({\r\n                'file': f.name,\r\n                'content': content,\r\n                'lines': content.split('\\n')\r\n            })\r\n        print(f\"Loaded {len(self.pulses)} pulses\")\r\n        return self.pulses\r\n    \r\n    def extract_patterns(self, text):\r\n        \"\"\"Extract structural patterns from pulse text.\"\"\"\r\n        patterns = []\r\n        # Section headers (invariant structure)\r\n        headers = re.findall(r'^#{1,3}\\s+(.+)$', text, re.MULTILINE)\r\n        patterns.extend([f\"HEAD:{h}\" for h in headers])\r\n        # Bullet points (variant content)\r\n        bullets = re.findall(r'^[-*]\\s+(.+)$', text, re.MULTILINE)\r\n        patterns.extend([f\"BUL:{b[:50]}\" for b in bullets])\r\n        # Code blocks (likely invariant process)\r\n        code_blocks = re.findall(r'```[^`]*```', text, re.DOTALL)\r\n        patterns.extend([f\"CODE:{len(cb)}\" for cb in code_blocks])\r\n        return patterns\r\n    \r\n    def classify(self):\r\n        \"\"\"Classify patterns as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n        all_patterns = Counter()\r\n        for pulse in self.pulses:\r\n            patterns = self.extract_patterns(pulse['content'])\r\n            for p in patterns:\r\n                all_patterns[p] += 1\r\n        \r\n        # Invariant: appears in >50% of pulses (structural)\r\n        threshold = len(self.pulses) * 0.5\r\n        for pattern, count in all_patterns.items():\r\n            if count >= threshold:\r\n                self.invariants[pattern] = count\r\n            else:\r\n                self.variants[pattern] = count\r\n        \r\n        return self.invariants, self.variants\r\n    \r\n    def predict_next(self, current_pulse_idx):\r\n        \"\"\"Predict next pulse content from invariants.\"\"\"\r\n        if current_pulse_idx >= len(self.pulses) - 1:\r\n            return None\r\n        \r\n        current = self.pulses[current_pulse_idx]\r\n        next_pulse = self.pulses[current_pulse_idx + 1]\r\n        \r\n        current_patterns = set(self.extract_patterns(current['content']))\r\n        next_patterns = set(self.extract_patterns(next_pulse['content']))\r\n        \r\n        # Predict: invariant patterns continue, variants may change\r\n        predicted = set()\r\n        for p in self.invariants:\r\n            if p.startswith(\"HEAD:\"):\r\n                predicted.add(p)\r\n        \r\n        # Calculate accuracy\r\n        if len(next_patterns) > 0:\r\n            correct = len(predicted & next_patterns)\r\n            accuracy = correct / len(next_patterns)\r\n        else:\r\n            accuracy = 0.0\r\n            \r\n        return {\r\n            'predicted': predicted,\r\n            'actual': next_patterns,\r\n            'accuracy': accuracy\r\n        }\r\n    \r\n    def run_experiment(self):\r\n        \"\"\"Run full TIC experiment.\"\"\"\r\n        print(\"\\n=== TIC Experiment ===\")\r\n        self.load_pulses()\r\n        \r\n        invariants, variants = self.classify()\r\n        print(f\"\\nInvariants (causal structure): {len(invariants)}\")\r\n        print(f\"Variants (accidental content): {len(variants)}\")\r\n        \r\n        # Test prediction on last 20 pulses\r\n        test_range = min(20, len(self\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 05:06:55\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774343222585}}
