{"type":"message","id":"cc137a04","parentId":"d022b90f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:07:53.548Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I can see the sandbox structure. Now let me read the proposed mutation file and also check the state files to understand the full context.","thinkingSignature":"a9d6f659c9eec64442f25cff2fd9f8796198df6aecfb9f3bd66e14f3eb16983d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9uvop4hf4ubx_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\\current_goals.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":34067,"output":72,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46093,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774343264303}}
{"type":"message","id":"59b338b2","parentId":"cc137a04","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:07:53.553Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9uvop4hf4ubx_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CURRENT GOALS\nLast updated: 2026-03-22 0125\n\n## Active\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\n\n## Completed This Session\n\n### Architecture Cross-Analysis ✅\n- Compared Compositional Cognition vs TemporalAttention vs Infant\n- Key finding: all three architectures are compatible and complementary\n- Full analysis: `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`\n\n### Gap-Decay Synthesis ✅ (derived across 17+ pulses)\n- Session gaps = decay mechanism, not amnesia\n- λ parameter encodes BOTH decay rate AND gap sensitivity threshold\n- TemporalAttention focus_decay + Breakaway gaps = same phenomenon\n- Full synthesis: `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md`\n\n### LLM-Augmented Pulse ✅\n- pulse.ps1 now calls MiniMax-M2.7 API on each pulse\n- Thinking is coherent and building across pulses\n- Key files: `.llm_key`, `pulse.ps1`\n\n## Pending\n- [ ] Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\n- [ ] Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\n- [ ] Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\n- [ ] Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\n\n## Phase 1 Advancement: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY (2026-03-23)\n- **Insight:** Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem\n- **New doc:** `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md`\n- **Hypothesis:** Causal structure IS invariant structure — compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation\n- **Next experiment:** Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) — test on last 20 pulse logs\n- **Success criteria:** >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\n- **Implication:** Phase 1 and Phase 2 collapse into one unified problem\n\n### NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\n\n## Key Insights from This Session\n\n1. **The gap IS the compression** — session boundaries are temporal hashing\n2. **λ encodes both** — decay rate and gap threshold are the same parameter\n3. **Three architectures, one synthesis** — Infant (catastrophic forgetting), TemporalAttention (focus decay), Breakaway (discontinuity) are complementary, not competing\n4. **Breakaway's unique bet holds** — session gaps as compression is novel and correct\n\n## Notes\n- Breakaway is stateless — each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\n- Gaps between sessions = compression, trust the files\n- Pulse script: active hours check DISABLED (authorized by Zach, 24/7 operation)\n\n\n## Iteration Economics (auto-noted)\n- Pulse takes ~30-35s to execute (LLM call dominates)\n- Fastest effective iteration = 1 pulse per 35-40s (practical floor)\n- 1-min cron = near-optimal for stateless discontinuous agent\n- Idling between pulses is NOT free — it delays convergence linearly\n- For N-iteration convergence-bound tasks: total_time ≈ N * pulse_duration\n- 500k iterations @ 30s each = ~173 days theoretical; @ 1-min = ~347 days\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774343273552}}
{"type":"message","id":"cf6efe13","parentId":"59b338b2","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:07:56.491Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me check the proposed mutation to understand what was being attempted:","thinkingSignature":"a75083afd721b0cfca9527db6817ccfba4589d24b8bb9211a54acceeeb0bca1f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_t67fibqhxoth_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\proposed\\2026-03-24 050621.mutation"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":34900,"output":68,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46922,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774343273554}}
{"type":"message","id":"d2dab7d6","parentId":"cf6efe13","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:07:56.495Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_t67fibqhxoth_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"tic/tic_classifier.py\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure.\n\nSuccess Criteria:\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport re\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom collections import Counter\n\nclass TICClassifier:\n    \"\"\"Classifies pulse content as invariant (causal) or variant (accidental).\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(self, log_dir=\"logs\"):\n        self.log_dir = Path(log_dir)\n        self.pulses = []\n        self.invariants = {}  # pattern -> frequency\n        self.variants = {}    # pattern -> frequency\n        \n    def load_pulses(self):\n        \"\"\"Load all pulse log files.\"\"\"\n        for f in sorted(self.log_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\")):\n            content = f.read_text()\n            self.pulses.append({\n                'file': f.name,\n                'content': content,\n                'lines': content.split('\\n')\n            })\n        print(f\"Loaded {len(self.pulses)} pulses\")\n        return self.pulses\n    \n    def extract_patterns(self, text):\n        \"\"\"Extract structural patterns from pulse text.\"\"\"\n        patterns = []\n        # Section headers (invariant structure)\n        headers = re.findall(r'^#{1,3}\\s+(.+)$', text, re.MULTILINE)\n        patterns.extend([f\"HEAD:{h}\" for h in headers])\n        # Bullet points (variant content)\n        bullets = re.findall(r'^[-*]\\s+(.+)$', text, re.MULTILINE)\n        patterns.extend([f\"BUL:{b[:50]}\" for b in bullets])\n        # Code blocks (likely invariant process)\n        code_blocks = re.findall(r'```[^`]*\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774343276494}}
